@717 = ~Fist of Iron~
@718 = ~Fist of Iron (Alteration)
Level: 1
Range: 0
Duration: 5 rounds + 1 round/level
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: caster
Saving Throw: none

This spell allows the warlord who loses his weapon to continue fighting. The warlord has to clench his fist while casting this spell, after which it takes the consistency of iron. As long as the spell lasts, the mage can't unclench his fist and can't hold any weapon, and has a 50% to fail casting of any spell he tries (he can not properly perform gestures). For most everyday tasks, he must use the other hand.
The Fist of Iron grants +2 to hit and inflicts 1D4 +4 damage points, but can not affect creatures that can't be hurt except by magical weapons. From level 10 of the warlord the spell is more powerful, the fist of iron is then considered as a magical weapon +1, granting +3 to hit and inflicting 1D4 +5 damage points. From level 15 the spell also increases melee mastery of the caster, granting him an extra attack and +2 to initiative when fighting with the fist of iron.~
