Range: 20 meters
Duration: 3 rounds
Casting Time: 1
Area of Effect: 1 creature
Saving Throw: negates

A spell is a straight attack against a creature that aims to stop it tracking the warlord. If it fails a saving throw vs. spells, it is violently shaken for 2 seconds, which has the effect of stunning it for the current round, and imposes it a -2 to AC, THAC0 and saving throws. At second round it puts itself back but still suffers the -2 bonus. At the third round the bonus becomes -1, after which the spell duration expires at the 4th round.
